1
00:00:00,457 --> 00:00:03,739
Well then, let's end our friendship now.

2
00:00:03,739 --> 00:00:08,216
<i>I've done it now... I've really done it now.</i>

3
00:00:08,216 --> 00:00:11,329
<i>With Kazumi of all people!</i>

4
00:00:11,964 --> 00:00:14,557
Maybe that wasn't enough after all?

5
00:00:14,557 --> 00:00:17,305
I'll try harder so you're satisfied.

6
00:00:17,305 --> 00:00:19,714
You idiot, Kazumi!

7
00:00:19,714 --> 00:00:22,457
So I was just a game to you?

8
00:00:49,147 --> 00:00:51,628
<i>I thought being best friends was fine.</i>

9
00:00:54,577 --> 00:00:56,144
I got dumped!

10
00:00:56,144 --> 00:00:59,131
Huh? But you two seemed so close.

11
00:00:59,131 --> 00:01:02,447
He said I wasn't what he expected.

12
00:01:02,447 --> 00:01:07,326
He wanted "someone more mature and refined".

13
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:12,570
<i>That sadness that she's hiding,
because she can't show her true self...</i>

14
00:01:12,570 --> 00:01:14,090
What about you?

15
00:01:14,090 --> 00:01:16,578
Someone asked you out again, right?

16
00:01:17,292 --> 00:01:18,930
Oh, right.

17
00:01:19,529 --> 00:01:22,980
Well, but I don't think I'll date them.

18
00:01:22,980 --> 00:01:24,760
Why?

19
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,115
Same reason as before.

20
00:01:27,115 --> 00:01:32,598
They have expectations,
and then leave when you don't meet them.

21
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,929
Huh...

22
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:40,892
<i>That unpretentious way she takes
my deepest feelings in stride with a "huh".</i>

23
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:46,421
Gosh, I wish we could just stay friends
and talk about everything.

24
00:01:47,703 --> 00:01:50,418
Then what if I became your boyfriend?

25
00:01:50,418 --> 00:01:51,776
Huh?

26
00:01:51,776 --> 00:01:53,107
No way!

27
00:01:53,107 --> 00:01:55,553
Then we wouldn't
be able to talk about everything.

28
00:01:55,553 --> 00:01:57,233
You think so?

29
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:58,628
Yes.

30
00:01:58,628 --> 00:02:02,127
<i>The words that come straight
from her heart, shown so innocently...</i>

31
00:02:04,118 --> 00:02:07,272
<i>Her smile,</i>

32
00:02:07,272 --> 00:02:09,525
<i>so bright and warm like sunshine.</i>

33
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:12,291
Could you take a look at it in advance?

34
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:14,195
Bring it over later.

35
00:02:14,195 --> 00:02:15,961
You're a lifesaver.

36
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:21,153
<i>She shows me expressions
she wouldn't even show her lover.</i>

37
00:02:23,001 --> 00:02:24,081
Why?

38
00:02:24,081 --> 00:02:26,411
That's what I want to know!

39
00:02:26,411 --> 00:02:29,766
<i>That was the privilege
of being her best friend.</i>

40
00:02:31,670 --> 00:02:35,256
<i>Rather than a relationship
that fades and ends,</i>

41
00:02:35,256 --> 00:02:38,525
<i>I'd rather be your one and only
unchanging person.</i>

42
00:02:47,906 --> 00:02:50,420
<i>But it didn't work out.</i>

43
00:02:52,572 --> 00:02:54,647
<i>That just wasn't enough.</i>

44
00:02:56,441 --> 00:02:58,417
<i>In that moment,</i>

45
00:02:58,417 --> 00:03:01,444
<i>I was confronted with a Himari I didn't know.</i>

46
00:03:01,444 --> 00:03:03,320
Wipe it, wipe it...

47
00:03:13,832 --> 00:03:16,284
Whether we're compatible or not,

48
00:03:16,284 --> 00:03:19,432
I don't think you can really know
unless you try it.

49
00:03:19,432 --> 00:03:21,800
<i>I realized that if we stay best friends,</i>

50
00:03:22,858 --> 00:03:25,604
<i>there are things we can never touch.</i>

51
00:04:26,655 --> 00:04:29,748
S-Sorry, did I wake you?

52
00:04:36,824 --> 00:04:38,985
Still hungover?

53
00:04:38,985 --> 00:04:41,007
Should I make you some breakfast?

54
00:04:41,007 --> 00:04:42,273
Huh?

55
00:04:42,273 --> 00:04:46,545
Wait... is this your place, Kazumi?

56
00:04:46,545 --> 00:04:48,792
You don't remember?

57
00:04:48,792 --> 00:04:53,115
You were drinking with Ando
and the others yesterday, and passed out.

58
00:04:54,842 --> 00:04:56,515
Oh.

59
00:06:08,425 --> 00:06:12,689
Wait, so... did we...

60
00:06:14,197 --> 00:06:15,779
Are you curious?

61
00:06:17,658 --> 00:06:20,266
Did we...

62
00:06:20,266 --> 00:06:21,757
We didn't.

63
00:06:22,676 --> 00:06:26,929
You were completely out of it,
so I held back.

64
00:06:26,929 --> 00:06:28,414
I see...

65
00:06:28,414 --> 00:06:30,086
Huh?

66
00:06:30,086 --> 00:06:31,674
<i>Held back?</i>

67
00:06:31,674 --> 00:06:34,664
<i>What do you mean, "held back"?</i>

68
00:06:34,664 --> 00:06:37,594
<i>So you're saying you wanted to?</i>

69
00:06:37,594 --> 00:06:39,008
Himari?

70
00:06:40,514 --> 00:06:48,155
<i>Wait, if I had a dream like that,
does that mean I actually...</i>

71
00:06:48,155 --> 00:06:49,650
Are you okay?

72
00:06:51,113 --> 00:06:52,759
I-I have to go...

73
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:55,960
I need to get home and get ready,
or I'll be late for work.

74
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,832
You don't have to rush off.

75
00:06:57,832 --> 00:07:01,913
No, thank you so much
for letting me stay! Bye!

76
00:07:06,862 --> 00:07:08,442
That was fast.

77
00:07:15,271 --> 00:07:19,210
I've got to tell her properly this time.

78
00:07:24,584 --> 00:07:27,832
<i>Having a dream like that...</i>

79
00:07:31,834 --> 00:07:34,661
[Vextos]

80
00:07:40,674 --> 00:07:42,897
Shibasaki, good morning.

81
00:07:42,897 --> 00:07:44,605
Morning, Ando.

82
00:07:44,605 --> 00:07:45,761
So, what happened after?

83
00:07:45,761 --> 00:07:46,895
Did it go well?

84
00:07:46,895 --> 00:07:48,122
Huh?

85
00:07:48,122 --> 00:07:50,149
I mean, with Hojo.

86
00:07:51,646 --> 00:07:54,593
I'm so sorry for the trouble the other night.

87
00:07:54,593 --> 00:07:55,841
No worries.

88
00:07:55,841 --> 00:07:58,881
So, any progress?

89
00:07:58,881 --> 00:08:00,355
Progress?

90
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:04,078
I mean, a guy and a girl
who missed the last train, out on the town...

91
00:08:04,078 --> 00:08:05,918
there's no way nothing happened, right?

92
00:08:05,918 --> 00:08:08,217
No, no, no.

93
00:08:08,217 --> 00:08:09,797
Really?

94
00:08:09,797 --> 00:08:13,890
You're not gonna say you had
a passionate night or something?

95
00:08:13,890 --> 00:08:18,449
No, me and Hojo are just friends.

96
00:08:18,449 --> 00:08:19,763
That's suspicious too.

97
00:08:19,763 --> 00:08:22,530
Honestly, it's obvious you two
like each other.

98
00:08:24,924 --> 00:08:27,391
The only one I act like this with...

99
00:08:28,262 --> 00:08:30,101
is you, Himari.

100
00:08:32,768 --> 00:08:36,430
<i>What did that even mean?</i>

101
00:08:37,716 --> 00:08:40,286
So really, nothing happened?

102
00:08:41,422 --> 00:08:42,743
Nothing.

103
00:08:42,743 --> 00:08:44,468
You know, you should've come too, Okada.

104
00:08:44,468 --> 00:08:47,011
I'll plan another one,
so make sure to drop by then.

105
00:08:47,011 --> 00:08:48,944
Sure, I'd love to.

106
00:08:48,944 --> 00:08:51,798
Everyone gets more hyped when you're around.

107
00:08:51,798 --> 00:08:54,923
No way, that's not true.

108
00:08:54,923 --> 00:08:56,593
Kurahashi, thank you for your help.

109
00:08:56,593 --> 00:08:58,662
Hojo, long time no see.
Thanks for everything.

110
00:08:58,662 --> 00:09:01,193
The section chief is in the meeting room.
This way, please.

111
00:09:01,193 --> 00:09:02,546
Thanks. See you then, Okada.

112
00:09:02,546 --> 00:09:05,006
Yes, thank you for your help.

113
00:09:10,556 --> 00:09:12,665
Shibasaki, Ando, good morning.

114
00:09:12,665 --> 00:09:13,732
Morning.

115
00:09:13,732 --> 00:09:15,764
Was that a client?

116
00:09:15,764 --> 00:09:18,763
Yeah. They're really nice to me,

117
00:09:18,763 --> 00:09:21,365
but I get a lot of personal invitations too.

118
00:09:21,365 --> 00:09:24,982
So Hojo has been acting as a buffer for me.

119
00:09:24,982 --> 00:09:26,435
I see.

120
00:09:26,435 --> 00:09:28,086
Being cute sure comes
with its own problems.

121
00:09:28,086 --> 00:09:30,289
No, that's not it at all.

122
00:09:30,289 --> 00:09:33,910
<i>I see... so that's how it is.</i>

123
00:09:38,206 --> 00:09:42,811
<i>But to think Kazumi might actually like me...</i>

124
00:09:42,811 --> 00:09:45,909
<i>Could that really be true?</i>

125
00:09:49,328 --> 00:09:53,442
I mean... we've been together for nine years,

126
00:09:53,442 --> 00:09:56,879
there's no way he'd suddenly like me now,
right?

127
00:09:58,956 --> 00:10:00,977
Like what?

128
00:10:00,977 --> 00:10:02,268
You scared me!

129
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,946
Don't just talk to me from behind like that,
my heart can't take it.

130
00:10:05,946 --> 00:10:09,056
You're the one who was spacing out too much.

131
00:10:09,056 --> 00:10:10,852
What were you thinking about?

132
00:10:12,432 --> 00:10:14,564
Work stuff.

133
00:10:14,564 --> 00:10:16,606
I should get back.

134
00:10:16,606 --> 00:10:18,554
Hold on.

135
00:10:18,554 --> 00:10:21,807
I didn't have time to say it this morning,

136
00:10:21,807 --> 00:10:24,475
but I've been thinking,
I need to talk to you properly.

137
00:10:25,439 --> 00:10:29,556
Can I grab your time tonight, Shibasaki?

138
00:10:30,336 --> 00:10:31,549
Huh?

139
00:10:32,404 --> 00:10:34,768
Before the girl I like slips away,

140
00:10:34,768 --> 00:10:37,676
I need to confess properly.

141
00:10:37,676 --> 00:10:39,502
You get what I'm saying, right?

142
00:10:41,948 --> 00:10:43,795
Huh? Wait, what?

143
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:50,954
But we have the department
drinking party today, don't we?

144
00:10:50,954 --> 00:10:53,357
After that.

145
00:10:53,357 --> 00:10:54,980
Let's go home together.

146
00:11:03,254 --> 00:11:04,771
<i>Huh?</i>

147
00:11:04,771 --> 00:11:06,180
<i>Wait...</i>

148
00:11:06,935 --> 00:11:12,236
<i>The person Kazumi likes... is... me?</i>

149
00:11:12,236 --> 00:11:13,896
No way...

150
00:11:27,539 --> 00:11:30,510
Shibasaki, your face is really red.
Are you okay?

151
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:31,889
Huh?

152
00:11:33,115 --> 00:11:34,921
I was just running a bit.

153
00:11:34,921 --> 00:11:36,174
Huh?

154
00:11:37,287 --> 00:11:39,895
<i>He's not supposed to turn this into romance.</i>

155
00:11:39,895 --> 00:11:43,419
<i>Kazumi was supposed to
just stay my best friend, right?</i>

156
00:11:44,354 --> 00:11:48,342
Shibasaki, want to go to
the drinking party together?

157
00:11:49,336 --> 00:11:52,590
Yeah, yeah, you're right. Let's go.

158
00:11:55,384 --> 00:11:59,723
<i>Anyway, I need to calm down first.</i>

159
00:12:06,325 --> 00:12:08,556
Our ace! Good work today.

160
00:12:08,556 --> 00:12:09,696
Good work.

161
00:12:09,696 --> 00:12:13,368
- Good work, good work.
- Excuse me.

162
00:12:13,368 --> 00:12:15,867
I'm glad we made it through this month
without issues.

163
00:12:15,867 --> 00:12:18,781
Thank you so much. The section chief's...

164
00:12:22,441 --> 00:12:25,552
<i>We're sitting so far apart.</i>

165
00:12:25,552 --> 00:12:28,574
<i>But that's fine.</i>

166
00:12:30,089 --> 00:12:32,842
Shibasaki, here you go.

167
00:12:32,842 --> 00:12:34,836
Thanks, but just a little.

168
00:12:34,836 --> 00:12:36,184
You can't drink much?

169
00:12:36,184 --> 00:12:38,811
- No, I just messed up previously.
- Messed up?

170
00:12:38,811 --> 00:12:39,956
Huh?

171
00:12:42,206 --> 00:12:43,402
How's work going?

172
00:12:43,402 --> 00:12:45,622
It's your second year,
so it's no problem, right?

173
00:12:45,622 --> 00:12:48,295
- No, I still have a lot to learn.
- That's not true.

174
00:12:48,295 --> 00:12:53,504
Your layouts have gotten better,
and your copy is more eye-catching too.

175
00:12:53,504 --> 00:12:55,251
You're just a good teacher, Shibasaki.

176
00:12:55,251 --> 00:12:58,478
Wow, that's nice to hear.

177
00:13:03,119 --> 00:13:06,074
Looks like they're having fun over there.

178
00:13:06,074 --> 00:13:07,854
Yeah.

179
00:13:09,464 --> 00:13:12,939
<i>Hey, don't act all composed
and drink like nothing's wrong!</i>

180
00:13:12,939 --> 00:13:15,076
<i>At least show some sign of being flustered!</i>

181
00:13:17,473 --> 00:13:19,653
Are you curious about them?

182
00:13:19,653 --> 00:13:20,955
Huh?

183
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:23,679
No, not at all.

184
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:28,872
So you and Hojo have known each other
since college, right?

185
00:13:28,872 --> 00:13:30,834
Yeah.

186
00:13:30,834 --> 00:13:33,294
And you just happened to end up
at the same company?

187
00:13:33,294 --> 00:13:34,506
That's crazy.

188
00:13:34,506 --> 00:13:41,100
Nah, my old workplace
was a total exploitative sweatshop.

189
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:46,048
And when I hit my limit,
Hojo recommended this place.

190
00:13:50,417 --> 00:13:54,618
But Hojo seems nice on the surface,

191
00:13:54,618 --> 00:13:57,945
don't you think you can't really tell
what he's thinking underneath?

192
00:13:57,945 --> 00:14:01,784
Like, he's got that smirking-cyborg vibe.

193
00:14:01,784 --> 00:14:04,326
Whoa, you don't hold back.

194
00:14:04,326 --> 00:14:06,633
Smirking cyborg.

195
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:07,873
You get what I mean?

196
00:14:07,873 --> 00:14:10,941
I can kinda see it.

197
00:14:11,731 --> 00:14:13,340
But...

198
00:14:15,031 --> 00:14:16,944
that's not true.

199
00:14:18,084 --> 00:14:20,536
He pays attention to people around him,

200
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:23,562
and I think he's kind.

201
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,820
- You like him.
- Huh?

202
00:14:30,820 --> 00:14:32,840
I mean as a person.

203
00:14:34,613 --> 00:14:36,952
Well... yeah.

204
00:14:41,602 --> 00:14:43,630
You're cute, Shibasaki.

205
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:45,602
You're so easy to read.

206
00:14:45,602 --> 00:14:48,248
Don't tease your elders, rookie.

207
00:14:48,248 --> 00:14:49,661
Scary.

208
00:14:54,368 --> 00:14:55,815
What's up?

209
00:14:56,509 --> 00:14:58,262
Nothing.

210
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:11,577
See you. You can walk, right?

211
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:13,131
See you.

212
00:15:13,131 --> 00:15:15,571
Next round, let's keep it going.

213
00:15:16,168 --> 00:15:17,475
I'm heading out.

214
00:15:17,475 --> 00:15:19,522
I'll take off first.

215
00:15:22,889 --> 00:15:24,215
You okay?

216
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:27,063
Yeah, I'm fine.

217
00:15:27,063 --> 00:15:30,515
Okay, Nihei, let's check around
for any forgotten items.

218
00:15:30,515 --> 00:15:32,209
Got it.

219
00:15:32,209 --> 00:15:33,683
Heave-ho.

220
00:15:33,683 --> 00:15:34,969
Whoa...

221
00:15:34,969 --> 00:15:37,730
If you're feeling sick,
you shouldn't push it.

222
00:15:37,730 --> 00:15:38,878
Want me to call a taxi?

223
00:15:38,878 --> 00:15:40,972
- I'm fine.
- Thanks, Nihei.

224
00:15:40,972 --> 00:15:42,457
I'll take care of Himari.

225
00:15:42,457 --> 00:15:44,828
I'll make sure she gets home.

226
00:15:44,828 --> 00:15:47,459
Got it.

227
00:15:50,956 --> 00:15:52,011
You okay?

228
00:15:52,011 --> 00:15:53,065
Yeah.

229
00:15:53,065 --> 00:15:54,919
I'll go grab your stuff.

230
00:15:57,551 --> 00:16:01,157
<i>The drinking party's over.</i>

231
00:16:09,934 --> 00:16:13,226
Don't do stuff like that.

232
00:16:14,253 --> 00:16:16,101
Stuff like what?

233
00:16:17,104 --> 00:16:19,818
Saying things like "leave Himari to me".

234
00:16:20,786 --> 00:16:23,986
You know, it might start rumors.

235
00:16:23,986 --> 00:16:27,356
I don't mind if rumors start.

236
00:16:28,322 --> 00:16:31,342
Because I want that kind of relationship
with you.

237
00:16:46,803 --> 00:16:50,564
I like you, Himari.

238
00:16:52,315 --> 00:16:54,175
I've always liked you.

239
00:16:57,846 --> 00:17:01,983
When I said let's end our friendship,
it wasn't some impulsive thought.

240
00:17:02,803 --> 00:17:05,065
<i>From the very beginning...</i>

241
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:09,022
We're drinking at Tomoya's place today.
You in, Kazumi?

242
00:17:09,022 --> 00:17:10,763
Nah, I think I'll pass today.

243
00:17:10,763 --> 00:17:12,270
Come on, don't be so antisocial.

244
00:17:12,270 --> 00:17:15,187
Sorry, invite me again sometime.

245
00:17:15,187 --> 00:17:18,071
Alright, fine. See you tomorrow, Kazumi.

246
00:17:18,071 --> 00:17:19,919
Yeah, see you.

247
00:17:51,006 --> 00:17:53,902
<i>From the very first moment I saw you,</i>

248
00:17:54,493 --> 00:17:56,481
<i>I've been in love with you this whole time.</i>

249
00:18:01,631 --> 00:18:04,326
I wanted to tell you that.

250
00:18:05,356 --> 00:18:07,090
I want to date you,

251
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:10,120
and I want to stay with you from now on.

252
00:18:12,537 --> 00:18:14,524
What do you want, Himari?

253
00:18:16,179 --> 00:18:18,441
<i>I had no idea.</i>

254
00:18:18,441 --> 00:18:22,615
<i>He never showed any sign of it at all.</i>

255
00:18:29,102 --> 00:18:31,296
I'm really happy.

256
00:18:32,266 --> 00:18:36,792
I want you too, Kazumi.

257
00:18:39,190 --> 00:18:40,584
But...

258
00:18:47,082 --> 00:18:50,152
Is something on your mind?

259
00:18:54,881 --> 00:18:57,031
Even if we become lovers,

260
00:18:58,328 --> 00:19:01,582
will we still be able to have
this kind of relationship?

261
00:19:08,099 --> 00:19:11,194
Then let's go on a trial date.

262
00:19:13,576 --> 00:19:15,695
Next time, just the two of us.

263
00:19:15,695 --> 00:19:18,713
We'll go on a proper date as lovers.

264
00:19:19,841 --> 00:19:24,470
And if it feels right,
we'll officially go out, okay?

265
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:36,953
Alright, it's settled.

266
00:19:38,342 --> 00:19:41,425
Let's take it slow and get closer.

267
00:19:55,117 --> 00:19:56,713
Hey.

268
00:19:58,322 --> 00:20:02,054
I know we're just a trial couple...

269
00:20:04,787 --> 00:20:06,474
But can I kiss you?

270
00:20:44,423 --> 00:20:47,359
<i>Even though I know it's just a trial,</i>

271
00:20:47,359 --> 00:20:49,347
<i>I don't want to let go.</i>

272
00:20:51,026 --> 00:20:53,890
<i>I'm the one who said it's a trial,</i>

273
00:20:53,890 --> 00:20:55,652
<i>but I don't want to let go.</i>

274
00:20:56,991 --> 00:20:59,984
<i>But that's not okay.</i>

275
00:21:01,644 --> 00:21:05,538
<i>If we really become a couple,</i>

276
00:21:05,538 --> 00:21:07,982
<i>then next time...</i>

277
00:21:13,499 --> 00:21:15,573
<i>- I want to be with you.
- I want to be with you.</i>

278
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,626
Are those two dating or what?

279
00:21:21,626 --> 00:21:23,008
Huh?

280
00:21:23,008 --> 00:21:25,253
I'll say this as a fellow new grad,

281
00:21:25,253 --> 00:21:27,788
but it's so obvious
those two like each other.

282
00:21:27,788 --> 00:21:30,256
Either they're dating already,

283
00:21:30,256 --> 00:21:32,439
or it's only a matter of time.

284
00:21:34,027 --> 00:21:37,701
Okada, what do you think of Hojo?

285
00:21:37,701 --> 00:21:39,857
Huh? He's handsome!

286
00:21:39,857 --> 00:21:44,700
He's good at his job, kind, reliable...

287
00:21:46,904 --> 00:21:48,318
What?

288
00:21:48,318 --> 00:21:50,824
Are you not on good terms with him?

289
00:21:50,824 --> 00:21:52,206
No.

290
00:21:52,819 --> 00:21:55,310
He seems nice on the outside,

291
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:58,985
but deep down, he's a cold rationalist.

292
00:21:59,665 --> 00:22:01,785
Rather than being kind,

293
00:22:01,785 --> 00:22:04,487
it feels more like
he just isn't interested in others.

294
00:22:05,794 --> 00:22:07,353
You think so?

295
00:22:07,353 --> 00:22:09,688
That's not how I see him.

296
00:22:10,548 --> 00:22:13,195
Earlier, when I was talking with Shibasaki,

297
00:22:13,195 --> 00:22:15,691
our eyes met with Hojo for a moment.

298
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:19,443
That look...

299
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:22,073
wasn't just jealousy.

300
00:22:23,312 --> 00:22:25,325
Don't tease your elders, rookie.

301
00:22:25,325 --> 00:22:27,143
Scary.

302
00:22:34,798 --> 00:22:36,371
What's wrong?

303
00:22:38,716 --> 00:22:41,975
It's totally baseless,
and just a gut feeling.

304
00:22:41,975 --> 00:22:43,673
But for Shibasaki...

305
00:22:45,005 --> 00:22:47,195
<i>if she does get together with Hojo,</i>

306
00:22:47,195 --> 00:22:52,461
<i>I have a feeling she might end up
really hurt someday.</i>

307
00:23:45,161 --> 00:23:47,341
You make such a cute face
in front of your lover.

308
00:23:47,341 --> 00:23:50,114
- Aren't you embarrassed saying that?
- Not at all.

309
00:23:50,114 --> 00:23:53,065
I don't think how long you've known someone
really matters.

310
00:23:53,065 --> 00:23:56,080
I don't think I can get along well
with someone who has too many secrets.

311
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:57,422
The things you want me to do, Himari...

312
00:23:57,422 --> 00:24:00,163
If I make all of them come true,
will you tell me?

